text: Albrecht Wehselau (born 5 November 1937) is a West German rower who represented the United Team of Germany. He competed at the 1960 Summer Olympics in Rome with the men's coxless four where they were eliminated in the round one repechage. ==References== == External links == * Category:1937 births Category:Living people Category:West German male rowers Category:Olympic rowers of the United Team of Germany Category:Rowers at the 1960 Summer Olympics Category:Sportspeople from Bremen Category:European Rowing Championships medalists
